to the editor re a speedy exit for linda chavez editorial jan 10 i agree with your assessment of president elect george w bush 's response to linda chavez 's flawed candidacy but your call for balance in the bush cabinet is laughable where was the balance in the clinton administration having gov christie whitman and gen colin l powell share the president 's ear with john ashcroft and gale a norton is a lot more balance than president clinton ever sought or wanted neil bardach new york jan 10 2001

